<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Hold Four Hostage in Durban House of Delegates </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hostage Drama Ends; 12 Arrested </H4>
<F P=102> MB1002203294 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 2000 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1002203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The hostage drama at Truro House in Durban is over. 
Twelve people were arrested a short while ago after the hostages 
were released. The drama started early this afternoon when 
three House of Delegates employees were taken hostage by a group 
of seven (Bunela) residents at Truro House. They demanded that 
charges of trespassing against them be dropped. They had been 
charged with illegally occupying houses at Cato Manor near 
Durban. The suspects will appear in court tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

