<H3> <TI>   Serbs Threaten NATO in Event of Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<H4>   Extremists Pledge To Attack UNPROFOR </H4>
<F P=102> LD1602145794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1348 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1602145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 16 Feb (TANJUG) -- Sinisa Vucinic, 
chairman of the Serb Royalist Movement [Srpski Rojalisticki 
Pokret, SRP], said in Belgrade today that if NATO launches air 
strikes on Bosnian Serb positions on 20 February, "a special 
unit of the SRP would attack UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] 
members in Belgrade." 
  He said that "the West should take this threat seriously" 
and 
that the SRP would carry out its threats regardless of the 
Serbian Interior Ministry's reaction. 
  Vucinic stressed that SRP members in Frankfurt were ready to 
"launch terrorist attacks on the German people" if air strikes 
were launched against Bosnian Serb positions. [passage omitted 
on SRP plans to launch a campaign against new folk music because 
of its Turkish sound] 

</TEXT>

