<H3> <TI>   Federal Deputy Escapes Bomb Attack Unharmed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1202000394 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 10 
Feb 94 Section 1 p 10 </F>

<F P=103> PY1202000394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The PP [Popular Party] federal deputy for Sao Paulo, 
Alberto Haddad, escaped a bomb attack in his political office in 
Pinheiros (western Sao Paulo). This information had been kept 
secret since 2 February, when the PM [Military Police] bomb 
squad was called. There are no clues on who planted the bomb. "I 
have suspicions about my enemies within the party," Haddad said. 

</TEXT>

