<H3> <TI>   Guerrilla Leader Alvaro Solano Captured in Neiva </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1302031494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1849 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1302031494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 12 Feb (EFE) -- Official sources 
reported today, Saturday, that Alvaro Solano, a Colombian 
guerrilla leader also known as "El Guajiro," who is considered 
to be one of the chiefs of the Maoist dissidents from the 
Popular Liberation Army (EPL), was captured today in Neiva, 
capital of Huila Department (in the south). 
  The sources added that "thanks to some information," police 
arrested "El Guajiro" at Los Garzones airport in Neiva as he 
prepared to board a domestic flight. The EPL dissident rebel, 
who did not want to sign the peace agreement with the government 
in January 1991, is being interrogated today by authorities. 
  Solano or "El Guajiro" is accused of rebellion, association 
with criminal intent, and terrorism, among other charges. 
  Last 29 January, authorities captured another rebel from 
that 
group in Cartagena de Indias (in the north) called Guido Meneses 
Ruiz, the alleged author of the murder of 50 former members of 
his organization who rejoined civilian life through the EPL 
agreements in 1991. 

</TEXT>

