<H3> <TI>   Government, People's Militia Sign Peace Pre-Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1502185994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1502185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sandra Vergara on the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Good afternoon. At this very moment, in the 
presence of Fabio Villegas, government and interior minister, 
the governor of Antioquia Department, the mayor of Medellin, and 
representatives of the People's Militia, a pre-agreement for the 
negotiation of a real peace process between the People's Militia 
and the Colombian Government is being signed. The members of 
the People's Militia have said that a cease fire will begin with 
the signing of this pre-agreement and that in the next 30 days, 
approximately 400 armed militiamen will surrender their weapons. 

