<H3> <TI>   EZLN Releases Former Chiapas Governor 16 February </TI></H3>
<H4>   Interview `Hours' Before Release </H4>
<F P=102> PA1602132594 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1602132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast; see SELECTED VIDEO REPORT in </F>
front of this Terrorism Report for footage of governor's release] 
  [Text] This humble shack became the home of former Chiapas 
governor General Absalon Castellanos, whom the Zapatist 
guerrillas kidnapped at the start of the conflict. Just a few 
hours before his release, Univision was able to obtain this 
exclusive interview somewhere in the jungle. 
  [Begin Castellanos recording] They told me to accompany 
them, 
and I went with them. By then they had blindfolded me and tied 
my hands. I remained that way in different places. I cannot 
tell exactly where, I couldn't tell until I got here. He [not 
further identified] held me responsible for these things, in 
addition to the death of leader Angulo [not further identified] 
when I served as governor. I could not answer those 
accusations. He said I knew.... [end recording] 
  Looking aged and with a humble voice softened by his days in 
captivity, the former governor now says he understands why 
violence broke out in Chiapas. 
  [Begin Castellanos recording] I do agree that social 
injustice really exists. Obviously they are greatly removed 
from civilization and there was this outburst. The outburst 
could have taken another form since the government has been 
willing to resolve all these problems. I hope the problem is 
resolved soon and that we think of ourselves as brothers, 
Chiapas residents, all of whom bear responsibility for this 
situation. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

