<H3> <TI>   Update on Jordanian Diplomat's Killing in Beirut </TI></H3>
<H4>   Suspects Named, Under Questioning </H4>
<F P=102> NC1102133194 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 1145 
GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1102133194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Judicial sources have revealed to our radio the 
names of the three Palestinians accused of assassinating Na'ib 
'Umaran al-Ma'ayitah, first secretary at the Jordanian Embassy 
in Beirut. They are Yusuf Mahmud Sha'ban, alias Wa'il Muhammad 
'Ubayd, whose name has already been announced; Bassam 'Abdallah 
Muhammad 'Atiyah; and Qasim Mihyu. The sources said that the 
accused Palestinians will be handed over for questioning to 
Sa'id Mirza, first investigating judge in Beirut, within the 
next few hours. 

</TEXT>

