<H3> <TI>   Update on Jordanian Diplomat's Killing in Beirut </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hirawi Informs King of Arrests </H4>
<F P=102> NC1102133694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1215 GMT 11 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1102133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yusuf Mahmud Sha'ban, who was said yesterday to be 
the assassin of Jordanian diplomat Na'ib al-Ma'ayitah, belongs 
to the Abu-Nidal organization [Fatah--the Revolutionary 
Council]. This report was confirmed today by a high-ranking 
security source, who said the murderer and three other 
Palestinians, suspected of being his accomplices in the 
assassination, are members of Fatah-the Revolutionary Council 
led by Sabri al-Banna, alias Abu-Nidal. The source said that 
the four individuals admitted that they are members of 
Fatah--the Revolutionary Council. 
  REUTER cited Brigadier General Staff Salim Salim, commander 
of the judicial police, as saying that the latest investigation 
into the case revealed that one of the three suspects is a 
woman, who is more of a witness than an accomplice to the crime. 
He noted that at first she declined to give particular 
information but did so later. The judiciary will determine the 
fate of each suspect. Security sources said the Palestinian 
detainees have been placed under strict security guard for fear 
that they might be attacked in jail. 
  President Ilyas al-Hirawi informed King Husayn of Jordan 
last 
night that the Lebanese authorities have apprehended the 
Jordanian diplomat's killer. He said the law will take its 
course. 

</TEXT>

