<H3> <TI>   Three Suspected Informants Killed in Gaza 13 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1402091194 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in English 14 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> TA1402091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alon Pinkas and Batsheva Tsur] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] In the Gaza Strip yesterday, 
the bodies of three Palestinians were found, all apparently 
killed because they were suspected of working as informants for 
Israel, Palestinian reports said. 
  One of the three was identified as 'Abd-al-Rahman Zino, a 
37-year-old ambulance driver from Gaza City. Zino, the father 
of nine, was abducted from his home last Friday. 
  Fatimah Abu-'Awdah, 55, from the town of Khan Yunus, was 
dragged out of her home by masked Palestinians and then shot 
several times. 
  The third was Qadir Dalamli, a 35-year-old taxi driver from 
Gaza City, kidnapped by masked men on Thursday. 
  Arab reporters said Dalamli's dismembered body was found 
outside his home inside a garbage bag. 
  The reports said Dalamli was believed to have been a drug 
dealer as well as an informer. 
  No group has claimed responsibility for the killings. 

</TEXT>

