<H3> <TI>   Beirut Paper Reports US Threat Alert for Tourism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1502193694 Beirut AL-DIYAR in Arabic 5 Feb 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> NC1502193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-DIYAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Badra Bakhus al-Fighali from Paris] </F>
  [Text] According to a senior Egyptian official, the U.S. 
ambassador in Cairo told the Egyptian prime minister: "The U.S. 
Administration has received information that terrorist groups 
are planning to carry out attacks against U.S. tourists in 
Egypt." 
  The official says this information was behind an alert the 
United States issued to its citizens concerning the possibility 
of attacks against them. The Egyptian prime minister told the 
U.S. ambassador that Egypt's competent authorities have no 
information or evidence in this regard. The prime minister 
asked the ambassador to provide the Egyptian Government with any 
information that Washington has on this so that the two 
countries might cooperate in facing any possible threat to 
tourists. Washington and Cairo are holding consultations on 
this issue. 

</TEXT>

