<H3> <TI>   Jihad, MB React to Islamic Group's Threats to Foreigners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1102094594 Cairo AL-'ARABI in Arabic 7 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1102094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-'ARABI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Khalid Salah and 'Abd-al-Fattah 'Abd-al-Mun'im] </F>
  [Excerpt] The mysterious "Islamic Group" statement warning 
and threatening foreigners in Egypt has drawn many reactions. 
In an exclusive statement to AL-'ARABI, Muslim Brotherhood [MB] 
Spokesman Counselor Ma'mun al-Hudaybi dismissed the statement of 
the so-called Islamic Group as "a stupid statement issued by an 
unenlightened quarter." The statement is unacceptable from all 
religious and human aspects because it harms the interests of 
the country, he said. 
  A person describing himself as a leader of the so-called 
Islamic Jihad Organization telephoned AL-'ARABI and strongly 
denounced Tal'at Qasim's statement, saying it provides an excuse 
for attacking Islamic groups. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

