<H3> <TI>   Iraq Said To Seek Bush Plotters Swap for Kuwaiti POW's </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1302154594 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People in Arabic 
1400 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1302154594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuwaiti Parliamentary sources have said that Saddam 
Husayn's regime is now setting impossible conditions for the 
release of the Kuwaiti captives in Iraqi prisons. One of these, 
they said, is the release of the 11 Iraqis now on trial in 
Kuwait in connection with a plan to assassinate former U.S. 
President George Bush. The sources said the regime also wants 
Kuwait not to refer to its prisoners as hostages or detainees, 
but as missing. 
  The sources said Kuwait responded through the Arab League, 
saying that the Iraqis who are now standing trial in Kuwait 
entered their country carrying weapons and bombs (?and tried to 
carry out) assassinations, bombings, and terrorist acts. They 
have confessed to this and are now in the hands of the Kuwaiti 
judiciary. The Kuwaiti captives, on the other hand, are 
prisoners and [words indistinct] because the tyrant's forces 
kidnapped them by force in front of their families and friends 
during the occupation. 

</TEXT>

