<F P=101> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Ambushes Shin Bet Car; 2 Wounded, Third Dies </TI></H3>
<H4>   Two Gunmen Involved </H4>
<F P=102> TA1302192394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1800 GMT 13 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1302192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Gunmen carried out an attack on three Israelis 
this afternoon near Ramallah. The injured Israelis, who are 
members of the General Security Service [Shin Bet], were 
transferred to hospital, while security forces have been 
searching for the attackers. More from Alan Ben-'Ami: 
  The three Israelis were attacked near the entrance to the 
village of Baytuniya beside Ramallah and about 12 km north of 
Jerusalem. The indications are that there were two gunmen 
waiting in ambush. The Israelis drove by in a saloon car and 
came under a hail of automatic weapons fire. Dozens of bullets 
penetrated their vehicle. One of the men was mortally wounded in 
the head and chest, the other two were both injured by metal 
splinters in the head, and one was wounded in the shoulder, 
while his companion was injured in the hand. [passage omitted] 
  A curfew has been placed on Baytuniya, the surrounding area, 
and parts of Ramallah as the security forces try to find the 
perpetrators of this latest attack. 
  [Jerusalem Israel Television Network Channel 1 in Hebrew at 
1800 GMT on 13 February adds that "Hamas has claimed 
responsibility for the attack." Later in the newsreel, the 
anchor announces: "It has been just released for publication 
that 28-year-old Shin Bet member No'am Kohen from Jerusalem, who 
was wounded in the Baytuniya attack today, has died of his 
wounds."] 

</TEXT>

