<F P=102> Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in English 15 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> Jerusalem </F>
<F P=104>  THE JERUSALEM POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] There is "more than one lead" in the hunt for the 
gunmen who killed General Security Service [GSS] agent No'am 
Kohen and wounded two other agents in Baytuniya on Sunday, OC 
Central Command Maj.-Gen. Yatom said yesterday. 
  Ramallah was under curfew for the second day, as reinforced 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] units pressed to find more clues. 
Sources said it is now almost certain that the attackers knew 
who they were ambushing. 
  Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] published a leaflet 
contending the attack was made possible through "a Hamas spy who 
infiltrated the GSS." The leaflet identifies the spy as A.A.H. 
  "A spy is the wrong term, but it is likely that a regular 
informant executed the attack, assisted by at least two others," 
one military source said. [passage omitted] 

