<F P=103> NC1202072194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The existence of a terrorism academy in Burj 
al-Barajinah [south Beirut] was revealed yesterday. Judge Nasri 
Lahhud, the government's representative at the Military 
Tribunal, has indicted the Palestinian Ghalib Husayn al-Jamal, 
currently in custody, on the charge of training individuals to 
carry out terrorist operations and manufacture the necessary 
explosives for such activity. Al-Jamal opened a school in Burj 
al-Barajinah, calling it the Academy of Terrorist Operations. 
He charged $50 for each lesson. 
  Judge Lahhud also indicted al-Jamal's brother-in-law, Mahmud 
al-Zu'bi, currently at large, for supplying al-Jamal with 
terrorist trainees over a period of four months. He referred 
the case to the military prosecutor. 

