<H3> <TI>   GPC Official Wounded in Attack in Maharrah 11 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1302104694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0515 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1302104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sanaa--[passage omitted] A responsible source at 
the Yemeni Ministry of Interior said last night that Colonel 
Yahya al-Jubi, director of political security in the Maharrah 
Governorate and member of the General People's Congress [GPC], 
was the target of an assassination attempt by unidentified 
gunmen who shot and wounded him near his house before escaping. 
Al-Jubi sustained several wounds in the attack, which took 
place the day before yesterday [11 February], according to the 
source. 
  The source indicated that Col. al-Jubi is currently in the 
hospital intensive care unit, and that the security agencies are 
conducting extensive investigations to apprehend the assailants. 

</TEXT>

