<H3> <TI>   Three Chinese Technicians Kidnapped </TI></H3>
<H4>   Abducted in Northeast </H4>
<F P=102> NC1302102194 Paris AFP in English 0910 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1302102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, Feb 13 (AFP) -- Three Chinese technicians 
helping to build a road in northeast Yemen have been kidnapped, 
Chinese diplomats said Sunday. 
  The three were abducted in a mountainous area while building 
a road between Hija, 127 kilometers (75 miles) north of Sanaa 
and Ma'rib, 173 kilometers (100 miles) east of the capital, they 
said. 
  No date was given for the abduction. 

</TEXT>

