<H3> <TI>   Explosions Rock Oil, Chemical Plants in Chechnya </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1634 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1302192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Groz'ny February 13 TASS -- Overnight, explosions 
shattered several oil and chemical plants in the Chechen 
Republic of Ichkeria. 
  According to the news agency CHECHENPRESS, shortly after 
midnight unidentified persons blew up three 2,000-cubic-meter 
tanks on the territory of the Goit-Yurt oil park on the 
Rostov-Baku highway between the villages of Mesker-Yurt and 
Belkata. Around the same time, another explosion damaged an oil 
pipeline on the territory of the Bufer oil park near the village 
of Tolstoy-Yurt. The fires caused by these explosions have been 
extinguished, except for one at an oil well outside the village 
of Vinogradnoye, 20 km of the regional capital Grozny, senior 
officer of the republic's fire department, Isa Khasimilov, 
reported. 

</TEXT>

