<H3> <TI>   Explosion at Gas Pipeline From Georgia Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1102221894 Yerevan SNARK in English 1327 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1102221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, Feb 11 (SNARK)--Tonight the trunk gas 
pipeline entering Armenia has been blown up again. The Armenian 
government's press-service told SNARK the explosion took place 
in the Marneuli region of Georgia, mainly inhabited by 
Azerbaijanis. The Armenian specialists have already left for the 
accident's place. 
  Meanwhile, it is reported that a day before the explosion 
the 
Georgian government had blocked the gas entrance to Armenia, 
motivating it by a scanty amount of gas entering Georgia. 
During the last two years about 15 sabotage acts were committed 
on this pipeline. Despite numerous appeals of Armenian 
officials, the Georgian government doesn't provide with the safe 
guarding of the pipeline. 

</TEXT>

