<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Letter-Bomb Suspect `Police Contact' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702133894 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 17 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1702133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DER STANDARD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["voel"-attributed report: "Letter Bombs: Detained Suspect </F>
Allegedly Contact Man"] 
  [Text] Vienna--On Wednesday [16 February] the Interior 
Ministry denied the allegation leveled by Joerg Haider, chairman 
of the Freedom Party of Austria, that the prisoner Peter Binder, 
who is suspected of having been involved in the letter bomb 
attacks and who is waiting trial, was a contact man of the state 
police. However, the Ministry had to admit that the state 
police had contacts with Binder before the attacks. The 
26-year-old man provided information on the desecration of the 
Jewish cemetery in Eisenstadt that led to the arrest of a 
suspect, who has again been released. 

</TEXT>

