<H3> <TI>   `Very Strong' Explosion Wrecks Truck in Athens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1702072494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0500 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702072494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A very strong explosion which took place at 0130 
[2330 GMT] today shook a whole neighborhood in Kallipolis, 
Piraievs. A small truck with license plate HH 1140, under which 
the explosive device was placed, was completely destroyed. 
There was also damage to three other private cars and the 
showrooms of shops and buildings up to 100 meters away. The 
explosion took place in Iakovos Rallis Street, where the owner 
of the small truck, Grigorios Kaflatzis, 63, resides. The 
truck's owner said that he does not have any differences with 
anyone. The antiterrorist unit arrived on the scene. 

</TEXT>

