  [Excerpt] A bomb exploded at the Tuzla train station in 
Istanbul this morning, killing four and injuring 40 Tuzla 
Infantry School non-commissioned officer cadets. 
  According to a TRT correspondent, Tuzla Infantry School 
cadets arrived en masse at the Tuzla train station to leave on 
their weekend vacation. The students, who were waiting for the 
train to arrive from Gebze, sustained various injuries when one 
or two powerful bombs placed in a garbage bin exploded. 
Forty-four persons, most of whom are seriously injured, were 
taken to various hospitals. Four of the injured died in 
hospital. They have not been identified yet. [passage omitted] 

