<F P=103> TA1602170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Midyat (AA) -- Eight people were injured when a 
bomb placed in front of a workplace exploded in Mardin's Midyat 
District today. 
  According to information that has been received, the bomb 
that was placed in front of a supermarket in the Orta Carsi 
neighborhood exploded around 1200 seriously injuring Hamit Akan, 
Huseyin Alpsoy, M. Ali Akyuz, Murat Orek, Ferman Akyuz, Hasan 
Topuz, M. Emin Alpsoy and Bilal Turkcan. 
  The injured are being treated at the Midyat and Mardin state 
hospitals and an investigation into the incident is underway. 

