<H3> <TI>   Delhi Reports French Offer To Help Fight Terrorism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1202114994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1202114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] France has offered to cooperate with India in the 
fight against terrorism. The external affairs minister, Mr. 
Dinesh Singh, who met the French interior minister, Mr. Charles 
Pasqua, in Paris yesterday outlined the problems faced by India 
due to terrorism. According to the Indian Embassay in Paris, Mr. 
Pasqua expressed full understanding and stated that France is 
prepared to cooperate with India in combatting terrorism. 

</TEXT>

