<H3> <TI>   Lebanese, Jordanians Held in New York Bus Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303081894 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0600 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Three Arab citizens were arrested 24 hours after an 
attack on a New York bus carrying a number of Jewish Americans. 
One was killed and three others were injured in the attack. 
One of the arrested Arabs is a Lebanese named Asad Baz who was 
charged with attempted murder. The other two, Malay Muhammad 
and Bassam Riyati, both Jordanians, are accused of possessing 
weapons and obstructing justice. 
  The New York police chief said that detectives found what he 
described as a veritable arsenal in the home of the Lebanese 
suspect. When asked if there was a link between the attack on 
the Jewish Americans in New York and the Hebron massacre, the 
police chief said that he did not rule out any possibility. 

</TEXT>

