<H3> <TI>   Nur Misuari Says MNLF Not Involved in Mindanao Terrorism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403111294 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Tagalog </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Moro National Liberation Front [MNLF] is not 
involved in kidnappings, bombings, and other terrorist 
activities in Mindanao. This statement came from Nur Misuari 
himself, MNLF chief, during an interview with our GMA 
correspondent inside the MNLF camp in Indanan, Sulu. 
  Prior to his departure for Tripoli, Libya, Misuari hoped 
that 
the long cherished peace agreement between the government and 
MNLF will be achieved. 
  [Begin Misuari recording in English] We are telling the 
people that it is not to the interest of the MNLF, nor to the 
interest of peace to create any unnecessary disruption to the 
peace process. That's why.... [end recording] 

</TEXT>

