<H3> <TI>   New Guerrilla Group Releases Wife of Putumayo Governor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2602021894 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2602021894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Aida Ruales de Laso, the wife of the Putumayo State 
governor, has been released after being held captive for 72 
hours by a new guerrilla group. According to reports from 
authorities, apparently a new subversive group calling itself 
the Putumayo Liberation Organization [Organizacion Para la 
Liberacion de Putumayo], whose members are EPL [Popular 
Liberation Army] dissidents, was responsible for the kidnapping. 
The objective of the guerrillas was to obtain money to 
strengthen their movement economically. 
  [Begin Ruales de Laso recording] I told them this was not 
the 
way to help the country. I told them that if we all worked 
together, but not the way they are doing things, Putumayo would 
advance. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

