<H3> <TI>   MRTA Political Command Leader, Narcoterrorists Captured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0103170494 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0103170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An important MRTA [Tupac Amaru Revolutionary 
Movement] political command leader was captured by Army forces 
in Bagua. The terrorist leader, identified as Humberto 
Pantaleon Campos, alias Seis por Dos, participated in raids 
against the towns of (Loindia) Grande and Jaen, and in a clash 
with the Army in Pampa (Cominca). 
  In addition to capturing the MRTA political command leader, 
the Army also managed to capture two alleged narcoterrorists, 
identified as Avelino Carlos Auiche and Miguel Iriarte Tellez. 
  In Amarango District, the 5th Infantry Division destroyed 
six 
maceration pits, four decantation pits, 20 hectares of coca 
crops, and various materials used to process cocaine paste. 

</TEXT>

