<H3> <TI>   Egypt Tightens Security for Israeli Community </TI></H3>
<H4>   Israeli Ambassador Receives Death Threats </H4>
<F P=102> JN0303094294 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 3 Mar 94 p 29 </F>
<F P=103> JN0303094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli diplomatic sources in Cairo have said the 
Israeli ambassador in Cairo has received threats that he will be 
killed if he does not hasten to leave Cairo. The sources added 
that all Israeli Embassy diplomats have received similar 
recurrent threats over the past few days in protest against the 
Israeli massacre, which killed and wounded a large number of 
worshippers at the Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  The AL-RA'Y correspondent has learned that the Egyptian 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs rejected a request by Israeli 
ambassador to Egypt David Sultan to bring in 40 Israeli security 
experts to enhance security measures around the Israeli Embassy. 

