<H3> <TI>   Abu-Nidal Group Appeals to Jordan's Husayn </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0103143994 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 1 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0103143994 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Ayman al-Safadi report: "Abu-Nidal Group Urges King Husayn </F>
To Give It Opportunity To Clarify Its Position"] 
  [Text] Amman -- Fatah-the Revolutionary Council (Abu-Nidal 
Organization) yesterday appealed to King Husayn to give it the 
opportunity to clarify its position on what it termed 
"allegations and lies" and "campaigns against it" launched since 
the beginning of the year. 
  In a statement distributed through the "Amal" group the 
official spokesman for the movement urged "His Majesty to choose 
the means that enable us to convey our view, its details, and 
the (case) file to His Majesty in order to acquaint him with the 
scale of our calamity, or -- alternatively -- this can be done 
via an Arab state or through an open letter." 
  The movement reiterated its denial of any involvement in the 
assassination of the Jordanian diplomat, Na'ib al-Ma'ayitah, in 
Beirut on 29 January. It pointed out that it was surprised that 
"the al-Ma'ayitah case was thrown at our movement." 

</TEXT>

