<H3> <TI>   Fatah Intelligence Chief's Brother Killed in Sidon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702070694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0615 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An incident has occurred in Sidon that might be 
linked to the Hebron massacre and the PLO's stand on it. 
Security sources in Sidon said that unidentified gunmen have 
assassinated Sidqi Farhud, brother of 'Ali Farhud, the Fatah 
intelligence service chief in the Sidon area. According to the 
latest information, gunmen opened fire from a vehicle at Sidqi, 
50 years old, and his 22-year-old son while they were driving in 
the Sidon port area. Sidqi died immediately but his son, who 
was slightly injured, managed to drive the vehicle to a nearby 
hospital. 

</TEXT>

