<H3> <TI>   FIS Leaders Released From Prison </TI></H3>
<H4>   Madani, Belhadj Released, Under House Arrest </H4>
<F P=102> LD2802142994 Rabat MAP in English 1334 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Algiers, Feb 28 (MAP) -- President and 
vice-president of the outlawed Islamic Salvation Front (FIS) 
Abassi Madani and Ali Belhadj, serving a 12-year jail term each 
since 1992, were reportedly released, Algerian daily `LIBERTE' 
said Saturday. 
  Certain sources said the two FIS leaders were put under 
house 
arrest in Douera (suburb south-east of Algiers) while others 
said they were in Zeralda (31 km west of Algiers). 
  According to the daily, other party leaders could have been 
freed last week. The releases, added the daily, are part of a 
general amnesty which is likely to take place before the end of 
the holy month of Ramadan. 

</TEXT>

