<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   AL-JUMHURIYAH Reports Arrest of 942 Extremists, Suspects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702173094 Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH in Arabic 17 Feb 94 pp 1, 14 </F>
<F P=103> NC2702173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hasan al-Shayib] </F>
  [Excerpts] In one of the largest search campaigns conducted 
by security forces in all governorates last week, 942 extremists 
and suspects, including 38 prominent terrorists, were arrested, 
274 kg of explosives, nine defensive and offensive hand 
grenades, 924 unlicensed firearms, and 2,360 pieces of 
ammunition of various types were seized. [passage omitted] 
  During the campaigns, 38 active terrorists were arrested, 
including fugitive Sa'id Muhammad Mahmud Hassan al-'Alami, who 
is suspected of being involved in the assassination of Qina 
Police Assistant Chief Major General 'Abd-al-Hamid Ghubarah; 
Chief Investigator Brigadier General Mahmud al-Dib, and State 
Security Officer Captain Muhammad Nada. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

