<H3> <TI>   `Militants' Shoot Policeman in Idfu; Police Kill Several Suspects </TI></H3>
<H4>   MENA Reports Three Killed </H4>
<F P=102> NC2802122394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1130 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aswan, Upper Egypt, 28 Feb (MENA)--Security agencies 
in the Governorate of Aswan, Upper Egypt, have exterminated 
three fugitive terrorist elements in a pursuit in the Idfu 
plantations area. 
  One of the three killed last night was fugitive terrorist 
Mahmud Abu-al-Majd, a resident of Draw. He was wanted in 
several cases in Aswan. The competent authorities are examining 
the two other bodies to determine their identity. 
  A conscript was slightly wounded during the chase. He was 
immediately given first aid treatment. 
  The three terrorists killed conscript 'Ali 'Abd-al-Fattah 
Abu-Hilb in an attack in front of the Idfu traffic department 
last night. 

</TEXT>

