<H3> <TI>   Small Bomb Explodes in Cairo; No Casualties Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103202994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2010 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Feb (MENA)--The Interior Ministry issued a 
statement tonight in which it noted that at around 1800 this 
evening, an unidentified person placed a plastic bag in a flower 
bed in the island in the middle of Murad Street in al-Jizah. 
The bag contained locally made gunpowder and silver-plated 
paper which caused an explosion. 
  The statement said that a fire brigade arrived at the scene 
of the incident and succeeded in containing the effects of the 
explosion, which smashed the glass front of a billboard above 
the flower bed. 
  The prosecution was notified to launch an investigation into 
the incident. 

</TEXT>

