<H3> <TI>   German Tourist on Nile Cruise Shot by Muslim Militants </TI></H3>
<H4>   Source Comments, Injured Named </H4>
<F P=102> NC0403140694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0403140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, 4 Mar (MENA)--A German woman tourist [as 
received] was wounded today when unidentified persons opened 
fire on the cruise boat New Jersey, operated by the Travco 
Tourist Company, between Asyut and Suhaj Governorates near 
al-Badari village. The wounded tourist was identified as Isis 
Gorjess [name as received], 54 years old. She was among a 
33-member German tourist group boarding the boat on their way to 
Cairo from Luxor. The boat sustained slight damage as a result 
of the shooting. Security forces surrounded the scene of the 
incident to search for the fugitive assailants. The Al-Badari 
Prosecution Office has started an investigation. 
  [In a related report, Cairo MENA in Arabic at 1325 adds: "A 
responsible security source at the Ministry of Interior has 
stated that at approximately 1000 this morning, unidentified 
persons opened fire at a boat in the Nile that was carrying a 
tourist group. The boat was coming from Suhaj and heading 
toward Asyut. A German woman tourist named Isis Gorjess was 
wounded by the flying glass resulting from the shooting. She was 
given first aid and transferred to Asyut University Hospital. 
Senior officials from the Asyut Security Directorate and 
various investigating departments moved to the scene of the 
incident for an examination. The prosecution has been told to 
open an investigation."] 

</TEXT>

