<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Persons With Pakistani Passports, Explosives Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0403093194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0403093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Delhi police have arrested six persons and foiled a 
well-planned conspiracy for creating widespread disturbances in 
India by Pakistan-trained militants. Briefing newsmen in New 
Delhi today, the city police commissioner, Mr. N.B. Kaushal, 
disclosed that they had planned to create disturbances, attack 
religious places, and use poison. He said it is for the first 
time that Pakistan used its own nationals for such operations 
who are trained and experienced in guerrilla warfare and 
insurgency. Sixteen kg of explosives, detonators, hand 
grenades, and Pakistani passports were seized from the arrested 
persons who belong to the Islamic Inqilabi Mahaz [Revolutionary 
Front]. Two sets of floppies were also seized from the 
terrorists, who were planning to prepare a computer. Cases 
against them have been registered, and they were remanded to 
police custody. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

