<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leader Escapes Murder Attempt in Florence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2802094094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1841 GMT 27 
Feb 93 </F>

<F P=103> BR2802094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Iran Opposition Leader Reported </F>
Attacked in Florence"] 
  [Text] Nicosia, 27 Feb (ANSA) -- The Iranian National 
Resistance Council said that one of its members in Florence 
escaped an assassination attempt yesterday. 
  In a statement to ANSA's Nicosia bureau, the group said that 
"two terrorists sent by the Khomeyni regime" chased one of their 
members in a car. The two, arrested by Tuscan police, were 
identified by the opposition group as Ayoub Fayoui and Iraj 
Oaderi [names as received]. 
  Last March, an opposition leader Mohammed Hossein Naghdidel 
[name as received] was assassinated in Rome. 

</TEXT>

