<F P=101> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion at University Reportedly Targets Saddam Mural </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802155694 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People in Arabic 
1400 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2802155694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A huge explosion shook the al-Waziriyah district in 
the center of the capital, Baghdad, yesterday, four days after 
three big explosions occurred in Karkuk. Iraqi opposition 
sources said the explosion yesterday took place outside the 
entrance of al-Mustansariyah University. They said the 
explosion targeted a big mural, which had a picture of tyrant 
Saddam Husayn, mounted outside the entrance to the university. 
Security forces rushed to the scene of the crime and the main 
entrance to the university was closed off. 

</TEXT>

