<H3> <TI>   Update on, Reactions to Hebron Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hebron Fatah To Resume Operations </H4>
<F P=102> JN2802100794 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 28 Feb 94 p 32 </F>
<F P=103> JN2802100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- The Fatah Liberation Movement in Hebron has 
called on the Palestinian command to immediately suspend 
negotiations with the Israeli Government at all levels until the 
settlers are removed from the occupied territories. The 
movement also announced the cancellation of the cease-fire 
between its combat groups and the forces of occupation, and 
herds of settlers and the resumption of operations against them. 
  The movement called on the strike forces to escalate the 
intifadah against the settlers and the army forces at all times 
and to consider any settler who passes in Hebron streets as a 
target for our strike forces. 
  The movement also called on national institutions and 
figures 
to halt all forms of contact with the departments of the 
military governor in Hebron, and held the Rabin government 
responsible for preparing and implementing the horrendous crime 
perpetrated by the settlers under the protection of the 
occupation forces. 

</TEXT>

