<H3> <TI>   Update on, Reactions to Hebron Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kakh Members Declare Hunger Strike, To Disobey Orders </H4>
<F P=102> TA0203122294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 2 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0203122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kakh member Barukh Marzel has declared from his 
hiding place that the four Kakh members who are hiding from the 
security forces this morning started a hunger strike to protest 
what they term the government's witch hunt against them. 
  David Axelrod, the Kahana Hay spokesman who resides in Kfar 
Tapuah, told our correspondent Gil Litman that yesterday he 
received an order restricting his movements and banning him from 
entering Hebron and Qiryat Arba'. He was also ordered to return 
his army-issued weapon to the IDF. Axelrod told our 
correspondent he will not obey the two orders and that he 
intends to come to Qiryat Arba' in order to visit the grave of 
Barukh Goldstein. Axelrod claims he should keep his weapon for 
self-defense purposes. 

</TEXT>

