<H3> <TI>   Bomb in Zuq Musbih Church Kills 10, Injures 40 </TI></H3>
<H4>   Fadlallah Denounces Bombing, Blames Israel </H4>
<F P=102> NC2702191394 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah called the 
bombing at Sayyidat al-Najat Church an atrocity and lamented the 
death of innocents. The bombing, he said, signals a new pattern 
of attacks on places of worship. He added that the crime is 
designed to disturb the country's security and political life 
and unsettle the public's renewed sense of civic peace. 
  Israeli hands cannot be absolved of this crime, whose 
purpose 
was to divert attention from the massacre at the Ibrahimi Mosque 
and trigger a new cycle of violence in the country, Fadlallah 
stated. He called on the authorities to uncover the evil hands 
that carried out the crime. 

</TEXT>

