<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Demands Rebels Release Kidnapped Aid Workers </TI></H3>
<H4>   Relief Commissioner Seeks UN Condemnation </H4>
<F P=102> EA0103161594 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0103161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Awad Khalifah, the commissioner general of 
relief and rehabilitation, has appealed to the United Nations 
and the international community to condemn the rebel movement 
and adopt a resolute stance towards its aggressive actions. In 
the course of an interview for our reporter, His Excellency 
confirmed that the rebel movement had detained five UN employees 
of Operation Lifeline in the Upper Nile area, saying that the 
rebel movement habitually violated its covenants and agreements. 
He said detaining UN employees while they were doing their 
humanitarian work was aggressive and barbarous. His Excellency 
condemned the movement for releasing the British UN employee and 
transporting him to Nairobi through the United Nations without 
saying what had happened to the remaining employees who are 
Sudanese. 

</TEXT>

