<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Said Planning Attack on St. Petersburg Mayor </TI></H3>
<H4>   Five Arrested, Leader Named </H4>
<F P=102> LD2502214994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1310 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Svetlana Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg, Feb 25 (TASS) -- Secret police in 
the second biggest Russian city said on Friday it had arrested a 
group of terrorists and found out that they had planned an 
attempt on the life of Mayor Anatoliy Sobchak and an act of 
terror against the government building in Moscow. 
  Head of the anti-terrorist unit of the St. Petersburg 
Counterintelligence Service Aleksandr Kuznetsov told reporters 
that on February 2 five terrorists were caught red-handed after 
they had seized five revolvers and 2,000 cartridges during an 
attack on the guards of the "Zarya" enterprise. 
  According to Kuznetsov, all the five participated in the 
armed opposition rebellion in Moscow last October. He 
identified their leader as Captain 3rd Rank in reserve Aleksandr 
Bogdanov. 

</TEXT>

