<H3> <TI>   Police Seize Weapons From APF Headquarters in Baku </TI></H3>
<H4>   Cache Found in Fire Inspection </H4>
<F P=102> NC2802190094 Baku AZERTAC in English 1440 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, February 28 (AZERTAC)--Seventy-three 
bullet-proof waistcoats, 200 bottles of incendiary liquid, 42 
artillery shells, grenades and other ammunition were found in 
the basement of the APF [Azerbaijan People's Front] headquarters 
by officers of a police department in Baku today. 
  According to Lieutenant-Colonel Gusseyn Allahyarov, the head 
of the Sabail police department, a few cartridges, one bayonet 
and three bullet-proof waistcoats were found during an ordinary 
inspection of fire-prevention conditions of the building. Then, 
by the city's general attorney's sanction, a search of the whole 
building was made and arsenal of ammunition was found. Criminal 
case instituted by this fact is under investigation. There is 
the general attorneys sanction to make a search of all strong 
points of the APF. 

</TEXT>

