<H3> <TI>   Police Seize Weapons From APF Headquarters in Baku </TI></H3>
<H4>   APF Rep Denies Coup Plan </H4>
<F P=102> NC0103191394 London Kanal-6 Television in Turkish 1700 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0103191394 </F>
<F P=104>  London Kanal-6 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Prosecutor-General Ali Omerov 
claimed that the Azerbaijani People's Front [APF] headed by 
Elchibey had been preparing to topple President Geydar Aliyev in 
a coup on 5 March. For this reason, 100 APF members have been 
detained since last Sunday. It was also noted that 42 rockets, 
explosives and an arms cache was discovered during a search of a 
building used by APF supporters. 
  The APF denied claims of a coup. One of the APF leaders, 
Nadzhaf Nadzhafov, claimed that the seized arms do not belong to 
APF. The police raided the news conference being held by 
Nadzhaf Nadzhafov at the APF headquarters in Baku, and sealed 
off the building. 

