Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed AdG: "`False Bomb Threat Was Work of </F>
Spanish Secret Service' -- ETA [Basque Homeland and Liberty] 
Suspects Deny Any Responsibility"] 
  [Excerpts] Brussels -- Luis Moreno and Raquel Garcia, the 
two ETA suspects who applied for political asylum in Belgium to 
no avail, heard the news of the bomb threat via Spanish 
television in their flat in Brussels. [see Spain, items 
AU2502115294 and AU2502165294 in previous Terrorism Report] 
Moreno and Garcia are certain that the threats are the work of 
infiltrators from the Spanish secret service. Earlier this 
month the couple appealed against the Belgian decision to not 
recognize them as political refugees. [passage omitted] 
  "They [the Spanish secret service] want to make the life of 
the Belgian Government so difficult that it has to deport us 
from the country," they said. "But we know better. If the ETA 
[Basque Homeland and Liberty] is planning an attack, then it 
does so through its own channels. At the bottom of the 
threatening letter they always put the standard round stamp with 
the logo of the independence movement. Not some Arab signature 
or other." [passage omitted] [see SELECTED VIDEO REPORTS in the 
front of this Terrorism Report for TV coverage of this incident] 

