<H3> <TI>   Authorities Uncover ELN Militia Plans for Bogota </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1103133994 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 7 
Mar 94 p 10a </F>

<F P=103> PA1103133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Agents from the Prosecutor General's Office and the 
Bogota Metropolitan Police yesterday uncovered an ELN [Army of 
National Liberation] plan to form a popular militia group in 
southern Bogota to meddle in the business sector and spread 
their ideological work. 
  Authorities raided a home in Las Delicias neighborhood where 
they reportedly found several pamphlets urging cooperation with 
the rebels and planning intimidation and extortion projects for 
various area businessmen. Seemingly, the ELN militia in Bogota 
would try to force people to contribute money, which would 
guarantee their security. [no beginning quotation mark as 
published] Three people were arrested in the operation, in 
addition to the seizure of Venezuelan arms and ammunition, as 
well as the pamphlets. 
  Authorities increased operations to try to break up the ELN 
plan and at the same time guarantee the fulfillment of a 
proposal by Ciudad Bolivar militias, who offered to demobilize 
and get their members to rejoin civilian life the way militias 
have been negotiating in Medellin. 

</TEXT>

