<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> GUATEMALA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sources Confirm Explosion of 2 URNG Propaganda Bombs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0603200194 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1630 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0603200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 6 Mar (ACAN-EFE) -- Official sources 
confirmed today at least two propaganda bombs from the 
Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity (URNG), whose leadership 
is negotiating peace with the government, exploded in the past 
few hours in this city leaving no victims. 
  The National Police Press Office told ACAN-EFE the explosive 
devices, filled with leaflets from the Rebel Armed Forces (FAR), 
one of four organizations that make up the URNG, detonated in 
two Guatemala City zones. 
  The source said the leaflets from the FAR, an armed group 
operating in the northern region under the leadership of 
Commander Pablo Monsanto, marked its "32 years of revolutionary 
struggle." 
  Several unidentified people dynamited the foundations of the 
San Juan bridge, which is located at km 20 of the Atlantic-bound 
highway, early this morning. The incident, besides causing 
property damage, created serious traffic jams. 
  The Army dispatched a delegation to the site to investigate 
if the guerrillas perpetrated the attack, which destroyed the 
bridge, and to estimate property damage. 
  The terrorist attack and the bomb explosions are occurring 
as 
the government and guerrillas are meeting in Mexico to end the 
oldest internal armed conflict in the region. 

</TEXT>

