<H3> <TI>   Chiapas Peasant Leader Killed, Bishop Threatened </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1003024394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1003024394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Live report by Mary Carmen Camacho in Tuxtla Gutierrez, </F>
Chiapas; from the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] 
  [Text] Once again, there is a lot of tension in Chiapas. 
There have been many protests by people either in favor or 
against dialogues with the EZ [not further identified], which 
are being held at the San Cristobal de las Casas Cathedral. 
Bishop Samuel Ruiz has received death threats. There is a lot of 
activity in Chiapas State. 
  Let us hear from Mary Carmen Camacho, who is in Tuxtla 
Gutierrez, the Chiapas State capital. Good evening, Mary Carmen. 
  [Camacho] Good evening, Pepe. Here is my report. Today, 
eight masked men killed Mariano Perez Diaz, regional leader of 
the Emiliano Zapata Peasant Organization. Francisco Meneses 
Gazon, municipal president of Simojovel, reported that the 
peasant leader was killed this morning on the doorstep of his 
home in El Carmito, 15 km from Simojovel. The son of the [word 
indistinct] leader in northern Chiapas was wounded in the 
attack. [passage omitted on labor issues] 

