<H3> <TI>   Yemen Official Denies Exporting Terrorists to Egypt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0403215494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2115 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0403215494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 4 Mar (MENA)--Yemeni Interior Minister 
Brigadier General Yahya al-Mutawakkil denied accusations that 
his country is one of the countries exporting terrorism and 
terrorists to Egypt. 
  In an interview with AL-AHRAM to be published tomorrow, he 
said that Yemen is targeted by terrorism and terrorists, 
especially the al-Jihad Organization and the Arab Afghans who 
have been discovered by the investigations to be behind a number 
of recent assassinations in Yemen. 
  He added that the brain and financier of terrorism in Yemen 
is Saudi businessman Usamah Bin-Ladin, who is wanted for trial 
in Yemen. 
  The Yemeni interior minister stressed his country's 
readiness 
to deport any Egyptian in Yemeni territory who is suspected by 
Egyptian authorities of being involved in terrorist incidents. 
He said that he will be the first to defend Egypt's security 
and stability. 
  Brig. Gen al-Mutawakkil revealed that Yemen prevented those 
who came from Afghanistan from using its territories as a 
crossing point, stressing that Yemen will never be a source of 
concern for Egypt. 
  Regarding the internal situation in Yemen, he said that he 
expects the military skirmishes in Abyan and Mudiyah to stop 
next week and the forces involved in the fighting to withdraw to 
their original positions. 

</TEXT>

