<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tehran, March 5 (AFP)--The Iranian parliament on 
Saturday [5 March] called for a Palestinian armed struggle 
against Israel until the Jewish state disappeared from the face 
of the earth. 
  "We declare that the problem of Zionism will only be solved 
through armed struggle against Israel until the cancerous tumor 
disappears from the map of the world," said a statement from 
deputies, read out in parliament. [passage omitted] 
  On Friday Iranian spiritual guide Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i 
called for a massive uprising against Israel, with the backing 
of the Islamic world. 
  Fathi al-Shiqaqi, head of the fundamentalist Islamic Jihad 
in 
Palestine group, vowed here Saturday that Palestinian militants 
would soon launch revenge attacks against Israel in retaliation 
for the Hebron massacre. 

