<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen Hands Over `Terrorist' Elements to Egypt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1003144794 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 10 Mar 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1003144794 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Muhammad 'Allam and Ibqal 'Abdallah report: "Aden Handed </F>
Over Group of 'Afghans' to Cairo"] 
  [Excerpts] Cairo, Aden -- [Passage omitted] In Aden 
authoritative political sources said yesterday that the security 
services belonging to the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] had 
handed over "terrorist" elements among the "Afghan Egyptians" 
[Egyptians who fought alongside Afghan mojahedin against the 
Soviets] arrested at the end of last month in Mudiyah, Abyan 
Governorate, with other groups of Arabs returning from 
Afghanistan to Yemen. 
  The sources said that "these Egyptians were handed over to 
the authorities in their country after proving their affiliation 
to the terrorist Jihad organization." 
  The sources, who asked to remain anonymous, pointed out that 
Brigadier General Muhammad Haydarah Masdus, deputy prime 
minister and member of the YSP Political Bureau, "handed over 
the Egyptians to security authorities in Cairo last week at 
Egypt's request after Cairo had heard of their arrest in Yemen." 
[passage omitted] 
  Security sources said yesterday that the "authorities in 
southern governorates intend to complete the investigations into 
the Afghan Arabs and then hand them over to the authorities in 
their countries under the Arab security agreement stipulating 
that terrorists be handed over to the states concerned with 
their trial." 
  As is known, the Arab Afghans held by the security 
authorities in Aden include Iraqis, Algerians, Sudanese, in 
addition to the Egyptians who were handed over to Egyptian 
authorities last week. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

