<H3> <TI>   Hamas Reject Using UN Forces in West Bank, Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503191494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0503191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on telephone interview with Islamic Hamas Movement </F>
spokesman Ibrahim Ghawshah by correspondent Muhammad Tishkar in 
Beirut; date not given] 
  [Excerpt] In the name of God, the merciful and the 
compassionate. The Palestinian Islamic Hamas Movement has 
announced that it rejects the dispatch of UN forces to the West 
Bank and the Gaza Strip in order to protect the Palestinians. 
Hamas Movement spokesman Ibrahim Ghawshah said in a telephone 
interview that this plan is designed to circumvent the basic 
problem, which is the presence of the Zionist occupation and the 
Zionist settlers on Palestinian territory. He affirmed that the 
PLO's purpose in making this suggestion is to attempt to tone 
down the escalating opposition among the Palestinian people 
inside and outside Palestine to enable the organization to 
resume its negotiations with the Zionist occupation. Ghawshah 
noted that the dispatch of UN observers will not ensure 
protection for the Palestinian people. Even if the UN Security 
Council decides to send armed forces to protect the 
Palestinians, he said, these forces will not be able to provide 
such protection. Proof of this is that thousands of UN armed 
forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina could not prevent massacres there. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

