<H3> <TI>   PLO Said To Order Fatah, Hamas Not To Attack Israelis </TI></H3>
<H4>   Fatah Members Asked Not To Attack Israeli Targets </H4>
<F P=102> NC0603111094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1040 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0603111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dubayy, 6 Mar (MENA)--Press reports published here 
today said that the PLO leadership has asked the Fatah Movement 
leaders inside the occupied territories not to take any military 
action against Israeli targets at this time. 
  AL-BAYAN cited Palestinian sources as saying that this 
request came in the wake of reports that reached the Palestinian 
command that some of the armed Fatah members in the occupied 
territories are planning with elements from Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] to stage widespread acts of revenge in 
retaliation for the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. 
  On the other hand, the same paper cited Hamas sources in 
Amman, Jordan, as saying that the group has agreed not to take 
military action at present and limit itself to civil 
disobedience and popular rebellion. 
  The sources added that Hamas agreed to this on the 
conditions 
that it be for a limited period of time and that this agreement 
would come after the PLO command informed it that there is an 
imminent agreement with the United States to provide 
international protection for the Palestinians in the occupied 
territories. 

</TEXT>

