<H3> <TI>   Gaza Hamas Leader Views Police Force, Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0903122994 Barcelona LA VANGUARDIA in Spanish 6 Mar 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PM0903122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Barcelona LA VANGUARDIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" interview with Hamas leader in Gaza Strip </F>
Mahmud al-Zahhar by Henrique Cymerman in Gaza city; date not 
given] 
  [Excerpts] Jerusalem -- [passage omitted] [Cymerman] One 
of the results of the agreements will be the coming of Yasir 
'Arafat and the establishment of a strong Palestinian police 
force. 
  Al-Zahhar: If this police force is here to serve 
the community, we will receive it willingly, but if it becomes 
the hands of Israel to establish a tyrannical regime in this 
area, I believe that they will do what Israel wishes. The 
people will endure no more tyrannies. They have resisted the 
occupation since 1967 and paid a high price -- thousands of 
years of imprisonment, thousands of martyrs. We seek the 
elimination of any kind of occupation. [passage omitted] 
  Cymerman: Will Hamas take part in the general 
elections for the autonomous entity? 
  Al-Zahhar: [passage omitted] Hamas will not take 
part in the elections and will not assume the role of opposition 
in the Palestinian autonomous entity. Hamas will continue to 
resist the Israelis' presence by all means. 

</TEXT>

