<H3> <TI>   Weapons Found in PFLP Leader Habash's Car in Jordan </TI></H3>
<H4>   PFLP Official Denies Story </H4>
<F P=102> JN1103134094 Amman SHIHAN in Arabic 12 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> JN1103134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SHIHAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Abd-al-Rahim Malluh, PLO Executive Committee 
member and Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] 
Political Bureau member, has denied the rumor that tried to link 
the movie theater bombings to the search of PFLP Secretary 
General George Habash's car, in which, the rumor alleges, 
weapons and silences were found. 
  In a statement to SHIHAN, Malluh said such rumors seek to 
harm Palestinian-Jordanian relations and to revive the past. 
Malluh said that tendentious parties are trying to link the 
bombings to the Palestinian factions in general to cast doubts 
on Palestinian-Jordanian relations, which are now being 
established on strong foundations. 
  He said Dr. Habash came to Jordan on 23 February on a 
private 
visit and was not searched. He was treated with all the respect 
befitting a pan-Arab struggler, Malluh added. 

</TEXT>

