<H3> <TI>   Two Citizens, 5 Terrorists Killed 6 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703175694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The security services today announced that two 
citizens were assassinated yesterday at the hands of armed 
individuals. The first was called Nadhir Ammar, 62 years 
mudjahid [liberation war veteran] who lived in the municipality 
of Boukaid, province of Tissemsilt. As for the second, he was 
called Aouni Nasser and was 54 years old and lived in Benkhedda, 
province of Tiaret. 
  On the other hand, the security services announced that they 
had killed five members of the armed groups yesterday in Bouira 
and Oran. In parallel to the escalation of the assassination 
operations aimed at various sections of society, the French 
language HORIZON newspaper today launched an urgent appeal to 
Cheikh Mohamed Sahnoun, chairman of the Islamic Call League, 
urging him to abandon his current silence and to work for an end 
to bloodshed in Algeria. 

</TEXT>

