Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "New GIA Chief"] </F>
  [Text] Sayah Attia has become the new chief of the Armed 
Islamic Group (GIA), replacing Mourad Si-Ahmed, who was killed 
by Algerian security forces in Algiers in February. Sayah 
Attia, who already was at the helm of several active GIA cells, 
is described in the local press as "the most violent 
fundamentalist terrorist." On Monday and Tuesday alone, three 
Algerian citizens were killed in Islamic attacks. 

</TEXT>

