<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Discover Cipher, Lists of `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503172994 Cairo AL-AHALI in Arabic 2 Mar 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> NC0503172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHALI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a clamp down on the hideouts of the terrorists 
Fawzi Mahran in Asyut and Muhammad al-Sayyid Abu-Zayd in Suhaj, 
the security forces found papers and lists bearing the names, 
whereabouts, and movements of a number of extremist organization 
members, including al-Jihad and the Islamic Group, since the 
beginning of last year. 
  The security agencies have also found the cipher 
organization 
members use in their communications inside and outside the 
country, in addition to booklets showing how to make explosive 
devices from simple material. 

</TEXT>

