<H3> <TI>   IG To Continue `Revenge' Until End of Ramadan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803171794 Cairo AL-SHA'B in Arabic 4 Mar 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> NC0803171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Group has announced that it detonated 
two bombs in front of the Nile Tower in al-Jizah, which houses 
the Egyptian-American Business Council, the International Bank 
of Commerce, and the Transmed Travel Agency. The group said the 
detonations were in retaliation for the criminal act committed 
in the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  A statement by the Islamic Group said the two operations 
were 
the beginning of what it termed revenge for the al-Ibrahimi 
Mosque martyrs and noted that revenge will continue in the end 
of the month of Ramadan [sentence as published]. 

