<F P=101> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosives Bound for Asyut Terrorists Seized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0603073694 Cairo AL-MUSAWWAR in Arabic 4 Mar 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> NC0603073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-MUSAWWAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Under the supervision of the public prosecutor, 
Counselor 'Abd-al-Sami' Sharaf-al-Din, the Higher State Security 
Prosecution is conducting extensive investigations into the 
seizure of explosives bound for terrorists in Asyut. The 
explosives consisted of approximately 100 kg of gunpowder used 
in making bombs and explosive devises. The prosecution is also 
conducting investigations to identify the source of these 
explosives. 
  In releasing this information, Counselor Sharaf-al-Din said 
the haul was found in the possession of two truck drivers. The 
two suspects admitted that a man, whose first name and 
description were disclosed, gave them two sacks of explosives, 
each containing about 50 kg of gunpowder, claiming that they 
contained organic fertilizer. The suspects said that he asked 
them to deliver the sacks to another man in Asyut after giving 
his description and fixing a rendezvous point and gave them a 
large sum of money. 
  The Higher State Security Prosecution ordered the arrest of 
the man described by the drivers and efforts are now under way 
to detain him. The two gunpowder sacks were delivered to the 
criminology laboratory for a technical report. 

</TEXT>

