<H3> <TI>   25 `Terrorists' Arrested for Bank Bombings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Suspects Part of Hajjaj's Group </H4>
<F P=102> NC1003171394 Cairo MENA in English 1548 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1003171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, March 10 (MENA)--Investigations conducted by 
the Supreme State Security Prosecution with terrorists accused 
in placing explosives at premises of banks in Cairo and al-Jizah 
revealed that the accused belong to Islamist group involved in 
the attack on a movie theatre in Hulwan. 
  The accused have confessed placing explosives at bank 
premises. They said they belonged to the group of a terrorist 
named Tharwat Hajjaj who was killed recently when he tried to 
open fire on policemen during his arrest. 

</TEXT>

