<F P=102>  TA1103110294 Tel Aviv MA'ARIV in Hebrew 11 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA1103110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv MA'ARIV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Rahamim Ya'aqov and Uri Arazi] </F>
  [Text] "We have been backed into a corner. We were 
ostracized when Rabbi Kahana was banned from being a Knesset 
member and when our list was prohibited from running in the 
Knesset elections. We are under serious pressure. I have the 
feeling that Dr. Barukh Goldstein's deed could happen again." 
  These remarks were made yesterday by a member of the Kahana 
Hay movement. "I would not be surprised," the man said, "if 
such an action were to take place within the walls of the 
Knesset, whose members blackball and persecute us. Look what 
one Jew did, and how effective it is." 
  At around 2100 last night, an anonymous caller phoned 
MA'ARIV 
and said that "500 Arabs would be slaughtered if Binyamin Kahana 
was not released from his prison cell in Hadera by midnight." 
  A check by MA'ARIV revealed that a similar anonymous phone 
call was received by the duty officer at the Hadera police 
station. The Hadera police have launched an investigation. 

