<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Institutes Death Penalty for Political Killers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703172894 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0703172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Council of Ministers, which met from 1100 to 
1500 today under the chairmanship of President Ilyas al-Hirawi 
and attended by Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri and the 
ministers, has decided to reinstate the law providing for the 
death penalty for those convicted of premeditated murder, and to 
extend this punishment to those who kill for political motives. 
  The Council referred to the Chamber of Deputies a host of 
draft laws designed to facilitate judicial work. These include 
an amendment of legal procedures with a view to shortening trial 
periods and speeding up interrogations in murder cases. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

