<H3> <TI>   Fatah, FRC Clash in Tyre Camp; Khirbat Silm Mosque Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803110094 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0945 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0803110094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to our correspondent in Tyre, clashes 
involving the use of machine guns and hand grenades occurred in 
al- Rashidiyah refugee camp at dawn today between personnel 
belonging to the pro-'Arafat Fatah and others from the 
pro-Abu-Nidal Fatah-the Revolutionary Council. Four pro-'Arafat 
personnel were injured in the clashes, including Major Abu-'Ali, 
deputy to the official in charge of military affairs in the 
camp, and his wife. The casualties were taken to a hospital in 
the camp. 
  Meanwhile, an explosion was heard in the Khirbat Silm 
village 
last night when unidentified men hurled a bundle of dynamite 
sticks in front of a small mosque. Tension prevailed in the 
village in the past two days in the wake of clashes between Amal 
Movement members and Hizballah militants after two cars and a 
home belonging to Amal members were bombed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

