<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Assassinated in Home </TI></H3>
<H4>   Group Named, Operational Details Listed </H4>
<F P=102> LD1103125294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1233 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1103125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By KHOVAR news agency correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe March 11 TASS -- The procurator's office of 
Tajikistan on Friday circulated a statement about the atrocious 
assassination of the republic's vice-premier Moyonsho 
Nazarshoyev. 
  The statement points out that the assassination was 
"committed in the Tajik capital by two members of an anti-state 
criminal gang headed by Mullo Kasym." 
  The assassins fled from the scene of the crime. On their way 
they stopped an oncoming VAZ-469 car being driven by a 
policeman. The criminals seized the policeman's gun and 
inflicted gunshot wounds on him. Later on the criminals 
attacked a food-laden truck, brutally beat its driver and rode 
the vehicle in the direction of Semiganch village of Kofarnikhon 
District. 
  The law enforcement agencies of Tajikistan brought it to the 
notice of the general public that Said Abdullah Nuri, leader of 
a self-proclaimed "government-in-exile," who is now in 
Afghanistan, had urged individual groups, who avoid prosecution 
for particularly grave crimes against their state to put 
vigorous pressure on the Tajik Government in order to 
destabilise the socio-political situation in the republic and 
fan up ethnic strife by using measures of intimidation, terror 
and physical removal of persons unwelcome to the opposition, 
particulary democratic-minded people and to work out plans for 
armed actions and other acts of sabotage. 
  The Tajikistan prosecutor-general's office has instituted 
criminal proceedings against the assassins of the vice-premier. 
A manhunt for the assassins was launched. 

</TEXT>

