<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Terrorist Said To Have Planned To Assassinate Reagan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803171094 Hamburg DPA in German 1538 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0803171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DPA) -- The alleged German top terrorist 
Johannes Weinrich obviously was planning to assassinate former 
U.S. President Ronald Reagan. This has been reported by the 
Hamburg STERN magazine [to be published on 10 March]. The 
Federal Office of Criminal Investigations [BKA] found a document 
among Stasi files in which Weinrich noted that the "President of 
the United States of America" was a targeted person and where he 
described the weapons he needed: "Two Beretta submachine guns 
and handguns with silencers." 
  Weinrich is regarded as the brain behind the attack on the 
"Maison de France," the French cultural center in Berlin. In 
the 25 August 1983 attack, one man was killed and 23 persons 
injured. It has been learned from legal circles in Berlin that 
the state prosecutor also has information that might point to a 
possible assassination plan. However, in this connection no 
preliminary investigations have been initiated yet against 
Weinrich, who is regarded as close confidant of top terrorist 
"Carlos." 
  The investigating state prosecutor in the "Maison de France" 
case has meanwhile confirmed that an international arrest 
warrant has been issued against Weinrich for aiding and abetting 
murder. In addition, another arrest warrant was issued in 
connection with Weinrich's role in the attack against the Saudi 
Arabian ambassador in Athens in 1983. The ambassador survived 
the attack only by coincidence. 
  The state prosecutor has further announced that he would 
soon 
request a third arrest warrant against Weinrich, namely in 
connection with the attack against "Radio Free Europe" in Munich 
in 1981, when many people were severely injured. According to 
the information of German security authorities, Weinrich is in 
Syria at the moment. The FRG has requested that the Arab 
country extradite Weinrich. 

</TEXT>

