<H3> <TI>   `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio </TI></H3>
<H4>   Suspect Refuses To Speak; Bio </H4>
<F P=102> PA2403135794 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0555 GMT 24 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 23 Mar (PL) -- The Attorney General's 
Office [PGR] today reported that Mario Aburto Martinez, alleged 
to be the gunman who murdered Revolutionary Institutional Party 
[PRI] presidential candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio, has said he 
"will not speak." 
  In a news release, the PGR said Aburto Martinez was born in 
Michoacan State, where he lived until he was 15. He said he is 
a mechanic and has four brothers who live in the United States. 
The alleged murderer of Colosio lives in the northern city of 
Tijuana, the scene of the attack that cost Colosio his life. 
Aburto Martinez described himself as pacifist and the author of 
several books on the subject. 
  The news release says the Harrison test applied on him was 
positive and that the attack was carried out with a .38 caliber 
pistol. 
  According to the PGR, Aburto Martinez said: I will not 
speak, 
even if I am tortured. 

</TEXT>

