<H3> <TI>   `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio </TI></H3>
<H4>   Preliminary Findings </H4>
<F P=102> PA2403143494 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpts] Raul Sanchez Carrizo reports that two people 
have been arrested in connection with the killing of 
Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI] presidential candidate 
Luis Donaldo Colosio. 
  You have already seen the two assassins on your TV screens. 
One of them is Mario Aburto Martinez. He is 23. There are two 
alleged killers. They are already under arrest. One of them 
fired at the PRI candidate. He is on screen right now. [video 
shows recorded footage of suspect being wrestled to the ground 
by angry members of a crowd; video also shows suspect being led 
away as members of a surrounding crowd punch him and pull his 
hair] He is Mario Aburto Martinez. He is 23. [passage omitted] 
  He said he is the author of pacifist books that he has 
already delivered to the foreign media. 
  Amid a great deal of secrecy, the Federal Attorney General's 
Office is also interrogating Vicente Mayoral Valenzuela, a man 
arrested as a witness [testigo]. Mayoral Valenzuela is also 
from the border city of Tijuana. 
  Attorney General Diego Valadez has been in that city since 
last night. 

